The paper deals with a graph embedding problem, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The problem involves partitioning the edges of a directed acyclic graph into pages and embedding the graph in a book-like structure such that each page is drawn without crossings and the vertices on the spine are in topological order. This problem is related to graph drawing (cs.CG), graph theory (cs.GT), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The complexity analysis of the problem suggests that it is NP-complete, which is a common topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS).
